FBIS4-21827 "jptot014__l94127" JPRS-TOT-94-014-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 27 March 1994 WEST EUROPE TURKEY PKK Bomb at Aya Sofya Injures Three Tourists PKK Bomb at Aya Sofya Injures Three Tourists One in `Serious Condition' TA2703124994 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1200 GMT 27 Mar 94 TA2703124994 Ankara TRT Television Network Turkish BFN [Announcer-read report over video] [Text] Three foreigners were injured when a bomb exploded in front of the ticket office of the Ayasofya Museum in Istanbul. According to our correspondent, the bomb, which had earlier been planted in the garden of the Ayasofya Museum in Sultanahmet, exploded around 1200. Three persons who were near the ticket office -- one from Germany, one from Spain, and one from Netherlands -- were injured. The German woman is reported to be in serious condition. The injured were taken to Haseki and Istanbul Medical School Hospitals. Extensive searches are under way to catch the culprits.
